tibetans hold deep antagonisms toward the chinese because of the communist government's past suppression of tibetan language, customs and religion
a coalition for democratic change beat pro-beijing candidates in this british colony's first territory-wide election in three years, the government-funded radio reported today
radio-television hong kong said candidates backing democratic change, such as the speedy introduction of direct legislative elections, won more than 50 of 74 contested seats in thursday's voting for neighborhood advisory board seats
although the boards carry no executive or legislative powers, their members are the only directly elected officials in the colony
the radio said pro-beijing candidates, numbering about 50 in a field of 459, did not do as well as the reform coalition. but no specific numbers were given
activists who sought direct legislative elections this year say the administration delayed the plan under pressure from china
under a 1984 pact, hong kong will revert to chinese sovereignty in 1997 when britain's 99-year lease on the bulk of the territory expires. the pact also says the colony's capitalist way of life will be maintained for 50 years afterward. warfare</head>
law enforcement officials are pressing for more federal funds to fight gang warfare in the nation's second-largest city, where seven more people were wounded in the last day
city and los angeles county officials received $2.73 million in federal grants thursday to help battle the gang violence responsible for more than 50 slayings in the county so far this year, police said
the grant will be divided between the city, which will receive $1.35 million, and the county, which will receive $1.38 million
but los angeles police chief daryl f. gates described his department's $949,639 share as ``teeny weeny,'' and mayor tom bradley complained that the federal government is ``in effect sending us out to fight a war with nothing more than pop guns.''
three suspected gang-related shootings left seven people wounded in the los angeles area thursday night
four people were wounded when a rifleman opened fire from a passing car in south-central los angeles, police said
two of the four victims were believed to be bystanders waiting to use a public telephone, witnesses told police. the apparent intended victim was a suspected gang member standing in a telephone booth, said sgt. rich gammel
i heard the shots and i went outside and i saw people lying there bleeding and other people trying to help them,'' said jason chung, owner of a liquor store near the shooting scene
i called the police and got my gun and went back outside. most of those people were my customers. they were just waiting to use the telephone.''
witnesses said between 16 to 20 rounds of ammunition were fired
none of the wounds appeared to be life-threatening, sgt. steve faulk said
the gunman apparently used a .22-caliber semi-automatic rifle, he said
in compton, southeast of downtown, two drive-by shootings about six blocks apart thursday night wounded three more people, including a 10-year old boy
the same car was described in both incidents, said compton police sgt. john garrett said. it was not known if the victims were gang members
gang warfare in los angeles gained national attention in january with the death of a woman who was caught in gang crossfire on a street in affluent westwood
the death spurred racial tension in the city after more officers were put on the streets in westwood. residents in poorer areas complained that police were overlooking daily gang activity in their neighborhoods
a train carrying segments of solid fuel booster rockets for the space shuttle collided with a car, but the rocket segments apparently were not damaged, nasa said today
nasa said that as a precaution, the segments would be examined thoroughly next week after they are unloaded
the accident occurred wednesday night in biloxi, miss., when a car collided with a chartered train transporting the segments to the kennedy space center here from the morton thiokol plant in utah. two people in the car died, police in biloxi reported
the train's engine was replaced and the segments arrived at the space center late thursday
the train was carrying three of the eight segments that will make up the two solid fuel boosters that are to propel the shuttle discovery into orbit. the launch is scheduled for aug. 4 and will be the nation's first shuttle flight since the challenger disaster more than two years ago
there was no apparent damage to the flight hardware,'' the national aeronautics and space administration said in a statement thursday
