the robbery occurred about 11:35 a.m. thursday when a man handed a teller a note demanding money, said seabrook police sgt. nona holomon. the note claimed the man was armed, but no weapon was seen, and the man left within minutes carrying the money, she said
a bank official followed the suspect in his own car, then alerted police using a mobile phone. three police cars followed the van and finally surrounded it, police said
