the women have been spearheading an opposition campaign to oust president hussain muhammad ershad, a former army general who seized power in a bloodless coup in 1982. their parties, the awami league and the bangladesh nationalist party, boycotted the march 3 parliamentary elections along with other major opposition groups
ershad's jatiya party gained a majority in the polls
