the sec alleged that between jan. 1, 1984 and july 31, 1985, paine webber charged its customers ``undisclosed excessive markups and markdowns not reasonably related to the prevailing market price.''
it said that the sales at issue involved ``stripped'' treasury bond coupons _ bonds stripped of their interest component and sold separately at a discount, a common practice of brokerage houses
